<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 5:40AM EST  by NWS Burlington</headline>
<description>...Pockets of Light Freezing Rain and Freezing Drizzle This
Morning...
A few pockets of light freezing rain and freezing drizzle are
expected this morning across the Champlain Valley, central, and
south-central Vermont. Pre-dawn temperatures are right around 32
degrees. Untreated surfaces may become icy until temperatures warm
above freezing by 9am.
Precautionary/Preparedness Actions...
The light freezing rain and freezing drizzle may quickly coat
roadways with a thin layer of ice that may be undetectable. Please
use caution...especially on bridges...overpasses and around curves.
Allow plenty of stopping distance and avoid braking suddenly.</description>
